e, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":75,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Thomas Harte was born about 1253, in Flixton, Suffolk, England, his father, John Harte I, was 29 and his mother, Mrs. Judith Harte, was 22. He married Lady Heydon about 1270, in Flixton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1329, in Westmill, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 77."},"et":{"about 1253–1329":"umbes 1253–1329","1253–1329":"1253–1329","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1225–1302":"1225–1302","1233–Female":"1233–Surnud","about 1280":"umbes 1280","about 1270":"umbes 1270","1253":"1253","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1302":"1302","1225":"1225","1233":"1233","about 1253":"umbes 1253","1329":"1329","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Flixton, Suffolk, England":"Flixton, Suffolk, England","Flixton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Flixton, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Westmill, Hertfordshire, England":"Westmill, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1253–1329":"noin 1253–1329","1253–1329":"1253–1329","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1280–Male":"1280–Kuollut","1225–1302":"1225–1302","1233–Female":"1233–Kuollut","about 1280":"noin 1280","about 1270":"noin 1270","1253":"1253","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1302":"1302","1225":"1225","1233":"1233","about 1253":"noin 1253","1329":"1329","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Flixton, Suffolk, England":"Flixton, Suffolk, England","Flixton, Suffolk, England, United 